---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout title="About Gloam" description="What Gloam is and how it works — a personal reading archive of the best writing from across the web.">

  <div class="about-container">

    <header class="about-header">
      <h1 class="about-title">About Gloam</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="about-section">
      <p class="about-lead">
        Gloam is a personal reading archive. It's where I collect and keep the best blog posts, essays, and articles I come across on the web — writing that taught me something, changed how I think, or that I simply want to be able to find again.
      </p>
      <p>
        Rather than bookmarks that disappear or reading lists that go unread, Gloam is a curated, browsable collection. Every post is saved in full, tagged, and linked back to its original source. The author and source site are always credited prominently.
      </p>
      <p>
        The name "Gloam" comes from the poetic word for twilight — that quiet time when you settle in to read.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2 class="about-section-title">How it works</h2>
      <p>
        The workflow has three steps:
      </p>
      <ol class="about-steps">
        <li>
          <strong>Clone</strong> — A Python script fetches the original post from the web, strips ads and navigation, and extracts the clean article content along with metadata (title, author, date, tags).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Convert</strong> — The cloned content is converted into an MDX file with a structured frontmatter block: <code>title</code>, <code>description</code>, <code>source_url</code>, <code>source_site</code>, <code>original_author</code>, <code>date_saved</code>, and <code>tags</code>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Publish</strong> — The MDX file is dropped into the Astro content collection and the site rebuilds. The post appears in the collection automatically, correctly tagged and linked.
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        The site itself is built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Astro</a> and deployed on Vercel. All styling is hand-written CSS with a teal-accented design system.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2 class="about-section-title">Sources</h2>
      <p>
        Posts come from a range of writing platforms and personal sites. The most common sources include:
      </p>
      <ul class="about-sources">
        <li><strong>Substack</strong> — Long-form newsletters and essays from independent writers</li>
        <li><strong>Medium</strong> — Technical and personal writing from practitioners</li>
        <li><strong>Personal Blogs</strong> — Independent writers hosting their own sites</li>
        <li><strong>WordPress</strong> — Established blogs and publications on the WordPress platform</li>
        <li><strong>Course Pages</strong> — Educational content from course sites and tutorials</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Every post links back to the original. If you're the author of a post saved here and would like it removed, please reach out.
      </p>
    </section>

  </div>

</PageLayout>

<style>
  .about-container {
    max-width: var(--max-width-prose);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .about-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-8);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .about-title {
    font-size: clamp(var(--font-size-3xl), 6vw, var(--font-size-4xl));
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .about-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  .about-section-title {
    font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .about-lead {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    line-height: var(--line-height-loose);
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .about-container p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    line-height: var(--line-height-loose);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .about-container a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .about-container a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-hover);
  }

  .about-container code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875em;
    background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 0.15em 0.4em;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .about-steps {
    list-style: none;
    counter-reset: steps;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--space-6) 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-5);
  }

  .about-steps li {
    counter-increment: steps;
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    align-items: flex-start;
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    line-height: var(--line-height-normal);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .about-steps li::before {
    content: counter(steps);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 1.75rem;
    height: 1.75rem;
    background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 12%, transparent);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 0.1em;
  }

  .about-steps strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .about-sources {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--space-6) 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .about-sources li {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    line-height: var(--line-height-normal);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
    position: relative;
  }

  .about-sources li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .about-sources strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
</style>
